{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GUI app or the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI — both backed by the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"},{"text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a future release.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook clone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instant copies.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Spooktacular.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"+","type":"text"}]},{"text":" button or press ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cmd+N","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a new VM bundle."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Managing-VMs","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CapacityCheck","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"important","name":"Important","type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","level":3,"text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"type":"text","text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProvisioningMode"},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","level":3,"text":"EC2 Mac Setup","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the planned architecture."}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc